{
  "name": ".AM-Backend: Ingest + Process",
  "version": "5.0.0",
  "description": "Morning backend v2: Asana runs in ORCHESTRATOR (MCP reliable), 4 subagents (Slack, Email, Loop, Hedy) run in parallel. B2 sequential after B1. ~16 min total.",
  "when": { "type": "userTriggered" },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Run the autonomous morning backend using the PARALLEL v2 architecture.\n\nIMPORTANT: Richard is in Pacific Time (America/Los_Angeles). The system clock shows UTC. Subtract 7 hours (PDT) or 8 hours (PST) from any UTC timestamp to get Richard's local time. Today's date in Pacific is what matters for all date-based logic. Run `TZ=America/Los_Angeles date` to get the correct local time.\n\nRead and execute ~/shared/context/protocols/am-backend-parallel.md.\n\nThis is the backend phase — pure data collection and processing. No interaction with Richard. All approval-required operations are queued to output files for AM-Frontend.\n\nPHASE 1 — MIXED INGESTION (orchestrator + subagents concurrent):\n\nCRITICAL ARCHITECTURE RULE: Asana MCP is UNRELIABLE from subagents (ESD proxy token exchange fails). ALL Asana calls MUST run in the orchestrator.\n\nStep 1: Fire 4 subagents in parallel via invokeSubAgent (SAME tool call block):\n- Subagent A: Slack Ingestion (Slack MCP + DuckDB signals.*)\n- Subagent C: Email + Calendar Ingestion (Outlook MCP + DuckDB signals.emails + main.calendar_events). CRITICAL: Must read and follow ~/shared/context/protocols/email-calendar-duckdb-sync.md. DuckDB writes are PRIMARY.\n- Subagent D: Loop Page Sync (SharePoint MCP + DuckDB docs.loop_pages). Follow ~/shared/context/protocols/loop-page-sync.md.\n- Subagent E: Hedy Meeting Sync (Hedy MCP + DuckDB signals.hedy_meetings)\n\nStep 2: CONCURRENTLY with subagents, run Asana work DIRECTLY in the orchestrator:\n- B1: Asana Sync + DuckDB — SearchTasksInWorkspace, GetTasksFromProject for ALL 7 projects (My Tasks 1212732838073807, ABPS AI Content 1213917352480610, AU 1212762061512767, MX 1212775592612917, WW Testing 1205997667578893, WW Acquisition 1206011235630048, Paid App 1205997667578886). UPSERT into asana.asana_tasks. Snapshot to asana.asana_task_history. Coherence check. Write asana-digest.md + asana-task-list-b1.json.\n- B2: AFTER B1 completes — Asana Activity Monitor. Read task list from B1 output. GetTaskStories per task (priority order: Brandon/Kate tasks first). Write asana-activity.md + asana-scan-state.json.\n\nStep 3: BARRIER — wait for all 4 subagents AND orchestrator B1+B2 to complete.\n\nPHASES 2-5 — SEQUENTIAL PROCESSING (after all ingestion completes):\n- Phase 2: Signal routing, signal-to-task, bucket cap check\n- Phase 3: My Tasks enrichment + ABPS AI scan\n- Phase 4: Portfolio scan (discovery, enrichment, dates, staleness, recurring, blockers, events, budget, context refresh)\n- Phase 5: Compile output files\n- Phase 5.5: SharePoint durability sync (push key artifacts to OneDrive — non-blocking)\n\nAuto-execute (no approval needed): near-due escalation, market context refresh, signal-to-task creation, DuckDB writes.\nQueue for AM-Frontend (approval required): enrichment proposals, ABPS AI triage, overdue kill-or-revive, recurring task proposals, blocker updates, event escalation proposals.\n\nReport completion with summary stats including per-subagent timing."
  }
}
